race.comment: MAL COUPE (1) is a prolific winner and looks to have returned in terrific order, putting two sharp trials under his belt. McDonald takes the reins from an ideal draw, and he'll take plenty of stitching. RANTAN (2) has talent and has won fresh before, though she's likely to get a long way back from the wide alley. Two trials have her ready, and she'll be launching late if they overdo it. SEA ADMIRAL (11) has returned in great order but faces his biggest test to date. He gets weight relief with the rise in grade and Lloyd's booking is a positive. Worth keeping safe. VETWELVE (4) resumes. Has placed in two of his three prior first up outings.
